===message:You do not KNOW that violence is not the answer, it is merely your opinion. The reason that you cannot come up with a viable alternative is because none exist. I am not advocating violence here. However, I am advocating war as a sometimes necessary solution to differences – which it is against extremism. Whether the number is 100 or 1,000,000 , the basic concept of war is not to kill or be violent. It’s intent is to break the spirit of one’s opponent by making him feel as if surrender is his only option. The casualties are only a byproduct of  the battles themselves. And when the spirits and ambitions of an Adolf Hitler or an Osama Bin Laden cannot be persuaded, they must be broken by force. Even you admit that negotiation, in these cases, is hopeless. So what other alternative is available?
