===subject:Lost Peace
===from:Ebony Mulero
===date:Tue Oct 22 10:43:28 2002
===message:I agree that war is not the answer in some cases and problems could be solved by negotiations. War should be used as a last result in a dispute between two countries. The disagreement should be talked out by the two countries in conflict by negotiating the issue(s), coming to a common ground, or agreeing to disagree and leaving the matter alone. If none of these can be accomplished then, yes, war is the only solution. At times you may have leaders who are willing to think things out and save the human lives of their country and if this is a case where there can be a resolution that will can take place. But as Robert Jones said if there are leaders and terrorist like Adolf Hitler and Osama Bin Laden then war is the only solution because people like this are not willing to work things out. It is either their way or no way because they will kill you. This is a hard reality to face, but not everyone is willing to do things in a peaceful manner and people who are not willing to need some kind of harsh action taken against them. I am in no way supporting war but I do think that sometimes this is what it all comes down to at the end.
